    public interface TaskInvocable<T>
extends Invocable<Task<T>>
    Describes the invoke methods of task vAPI operations.

    • Method Detail

      • invoke

        CompletionStageFuture<Task<T>> invoke()
        Asynchronous method. Result of the invocation will be returned as a CompletionStageFuture. Once the server returns a value the future will be completed. The result of the invocation is a Task object which holds taskId and return type of the operation.
        Specified by:
        invoke in interface Invocable<Task<T>>
        Returns:
        CompletionStageFuture which holds Task object with the taskId of the operation invocation.

      • invoke

        CompletionStageFuture<Task<T>> invoke(InvocationConfig invocationConfig)
        Asynchronous method with InvocationConfig. Result of the invocation will be returned as a CompletionStageFuture. Once the server returns a value the future will be completed. The result of the invocation is a Task object which holds taskId and return type of the operation.
        Specified by:
        invoke in interface Invocable<Task<T>>
        Parameters:
        invocationConfig - used for the operation invocation.
        Returns:
        CompletionStageFuture which holds Task object with the taskId of the operation invocation.
